column5: Just an FYI for anybody using the causeway ramp this weekend, the dock still hasn't been put in so if your by yourself it could be a bit of an issue putting your boat somewhere while parking your truck.
just reef'er up on shore...but not so high you can't push'er back out!

Just an FYI for anybody using the causeway ramp this weekend, the dock still hasn't been put in so if your by yourself it could be a bit of an issue putting your boat somewhere while parking your truck.    Good heads up Lew for those that are heading out there..  Thats why you have to have a good pal that can  back ya in,and take ya out.  Dont fish alone.LOL  Here in Barrie,all docks are in,heck,they never take them out.LOL
just reef'er up on shore...but not so high you can't push'er back out!  You dont reefer up Lews boat. You,ll scratch the gel.
I think it's a rock wall there around the ramp. Nowhere to beach the boat.
